A few years ago after reading Contrary Pancake posts about the Pacific War I would go to my grandfather's apartment and ask him if it's true no one expected the war to end after the nukes were used and everyone thought it would go on for years and he remembered it that way too.
Incredible privilege to be able to speak with someone who remembers historic events and was actually alive when it all happened.

A few weeks ago I posted about how in Pushkin's time there was a big overlap between freemasons and card game sharks/hustlers. Recently in a Galkovsky article I encountered this 18th century guy, Magnitsky, a prominent mason notorious for humorous buffoonery at lodge gatherings.

He really looks the same as Teller. The Wikipedia page (none exists in English) calls him an extreme obscurantist. He basically dedicated his life to trolling the Russian government by sabotaging universities, forcing students to study fake subjects, writing ironic essays, etc.
